  <name>ares</name>
  <summary>Multi-system console emulation suite</summary>
  <description>
    <p>ares is a cross-platform, open source, multi-system emulator, focusing on accuracy and preservation.</p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Highly accurate, state-of-the-art emulation of numerous retro systems.</li>
      <li>Support for the RetroArch family of 'slang' shaders via librashader. Enjoy advanced shaders from multiple families of CRTs, handhelds, and more.</li>
      <li>Rewind and fast-forward.</li>
      <li>Exacting pixel accuracy modes to faithfully reproduce original console color output.</li>
      <li>Full support for savestates; easily save your progress and pick up where you left off.</li>
      <li>Advanced latency reduction via "Run-Ahead".</li>
      <li>Support for multiple input drivers, including SDL3 for optimal controller compatibility.</li>
      <li>Complete game databases and smart heuristics for "plug-and-play;" no lengthy up-front system configuration required.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>ares currently emulates the following systems:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Super Famicom (SNES) </li>
      <li>Famicom + Famicom Disk System (NES)</li>
      <li>Nintendo 64</li>
      <li>Game Boy + Game Boy Color</li>
      <li>Game Boy Advance</li>
      <li>SG-1000</li>
      <li>Master System</li>
      <li>Game Gear</li>
      <li>Mega Drive</li>
      <li>Mega CD</li>
      <li>Mega 32X</li>
      <li>PlayStation</li>
      <li>PC Engine + PC Engine CD + SuperGrafx</li>
      <li>Neo Geo AES</li>
      <li>MSX + MSX 2</li>
      <li>ColecoVision</li>
      <li>Neo Geo Pocket + Neo Geo Pocket Color</li>
      <li>WonderSwan + WonderSwan Color + Pocket Challenge V2</li>
      <li>Aleck 64</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
